Trivial Cite is a very capable Citation package, much simpler than SuperCite, and helps to stomp out that horrible "initials" quoting style: CL> foo was here

* You can find some more information at http://shasta.cs.uiuc.edu/~lrclause/tc.html
* Download it at: http://shasta.cs.uiuc.edu/~lrclause/tc.el
* Mailing list: http://shasta.cs.uiuc.edu/cgi-bin/mailman/listinfo/trivial-cite-users

Note: The above links no longer work.  Does anyone know where to get the latest version?  The latest I have is 0.12; I can post it here if desired.

